<h2> Intercepted 100 Iran drones outside Israel by the US and Great Britain
More than 100 Iranian drones have already been intercepted by the United States and Great Britain outside Israeli airspace. It was reported on the Army radio by an Israeli defense officer on the Army radio, according to the Times of Israel.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> The EU condemns Iran's attack, "Escalation unprecedented"</h2>
The High Representative of the European Union for Foreign Affairs and Security, Josep Borrell, expressed "conflict condemnation" for the Iranian attack on Israel. "The EU strongly condemns the unacceptable Iranian attack on Israel," wrote Borrell on X, "this is an unprecedented escalation and a serious threat to regional security."
<h2> Iran to the USA: "By the conflict with Israel"</h2>
"If Israel commits another mistake, the response of Iran will be considerably more severe. It is a conflict between Iran and the Israeli rogue regime, from which the United States must stay away." It writes on X the permanent representation of Iran to the United Nations. The appeal to Americans to stay away is written in a dull character. &nbsp;
<h2> Iranian missiles will hit Golan and air base in Negev</h2>
The drones and missiles that Iran has launched against Israel will strike the Golan Heights - at the border between Israel, Lebanon, Jordan and Syria - and an Israeli air base in the Negev desert, in southern Israel. The New York Times reports it.
<h2>Crosetto: "The attack can cause a dramatic escalation"</h2>
"I receive constant updates and I follow with apprehension what is happening in the Middle East. They firmly condemn the attack of Iran and its allies against Israel, an unprecedented action that can cause dramatic escalation. We continue to work to avoid it." This is what the Minister of Defense wrote about "X", Guido Crosetto.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2>Teheran: "It is the response to the aggression of the Zionist regime"</h2>
"By virtue of Article 51 of the United Nations Charter on legitimate defence, Iran's military action is in response to the aggression of the Zionist regime against our diplomatic offices in Damascus." It writes on X the permanent representation of Iran to the United Nations.
Egypt calls for "maximum moderation"
The Egyptian Foreign Ministry expressed "profound concern" for the ongoing escalation between Iran and Israel and asked the parties to exercise the "maximum moderation". The agency Anadolu.&nbsp reports it;
<h2>Biden brings together the National Security Council
The meeting began at the White House in the Situation Room, the emergency room, between the President of the United States, Joe Biden, and the National Security Advisors. Reuters mentions government sources.&nbsp;
<h2>Hezbollah announces missile launch against Golan</h2>
The Lebanese pro-Iranian militia Hezbollah announced it launched missiles against the Golan, occupied by Israel.
<h2> From Yemen Houthi launch drones on Israel</h2>
The Houthi rebels of Yemen launched several drones against Israel in coordination with Iran, declared it the Ambrey security company, adding that the bullets were probably planned to reach Israel at the same time.
&nbsp;
<div </div
<br> "The pilotless air vehicles (UAV) would have been launched by the Huthi to Israel. The UAVs were launched in coordination with Iran," said the company. "The Israeli ports are considered potential objectives", added the society, which warned from " collateral damages" to the marine transport.
&nbsp;
<h2> Iran threatens those who open air space to support Israel
Iran's Minister of Defense, Reza Ashtiani, warned that Tehran will respond firmly to any country "open its air space or territory for Israeli attacks against Iran". It is reported by the Iranian semi-official agency Mehr, relaunched by the Times of Israel.&nbsp;
<h2> Iran and allies will launch 400-500 drones and missiles
The American government believes that Iran will launch 400-500 drones and missiles from its territory and from countries such as Iraq, Syria and southern Lebanon, where Iranian militias or allies of Tehran are present. Abc News reports, specifying that most will be launched by Iran.&nbsp;
<h2> France condemns Iran's attack on Israel
France condemns Iran's attack on Israel, which "carrys its destabilizing actions to a new level", said Foreign Minister Stephane Sejourne on X.<br> "Deciding to take an unprecedented action, Iran is overcoming a new threshold in its destabilizing actions and runs the risk of military escalation," he wrote, adding that "France reaffirms its attachment to Israel's security and assures it its solidarity".
<h2>Sunak: "The Iranian attack is undesirable"</h2>
Britain condemns Iran's attack on Israel, said British Prime Minister Rishi Sunak in a statement published on X. "They firmly condemn the undesirable attack of the Iranian regime against Israel. Iran has once again shown that it is willing to sow chaos in its own courtyard," says.<br> Great Britain "will continue to defend the security of Israel and that of all our regional partners, including Jordan and Iraq." "With our allies, we are working urgently to stabilize the situation and prevent further escalation. Nobody wants to see more bloodshed." &nbsp;
<h2> Back from Lebanon, sirens explained in kibbutz Israel</h2>
The alarm sirens resound in the community of Snir, in the North of Israel, due to an attack with rockets from Lebanon. The Times of Israel reports it, recalling that Hezbollah carried out several attacks in Northern Israel during the Gaza Strip war. There is no immediate news of damage or injury in the attack.
<h2> Egyptian air defence at maximum alert </h2>
The Egyptian Air Defense is in maximum alert after the attack launched by Iran with drones and cruise missiles against Israel. Local media report it.
<h2>Khamenei, Israel will be punished
"The wicked Zionist regime will be punished," said the Iranian supreme leader Sayyid Ali Khamenei on X.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2>Biden in the room. The attack will last hours</h2>
The White House confirmed the beginning of a "aircraft" attack by Iran against Israel and assured that the operation "will probably take place within several hours", while President Joe Biden, who interrupted his weekend break, is informed. "Iran started an air strike against Israel. President Biden is regularly updated on the situation from his national security team and will meet with them this afternoon at the White House," said the White House in a statement.
According to the United States, these attacks "will probably take place within several hours." According to U.S. intelligence sources consulted by CNN, the attack began with a wave of drones targeting different points to make the effective response of Israeli air defense difficult.<br> "President Biden was clear: Our support for Israel's security is unwavering. The United States will be at the side of the Israeli people and will support its defence against Iran's threats," said the White House.<br> Biden will meet in the Situation Room with Secretary of Defense Lloyd Austin, Secretary of State Antony Blinken, CIA Director Bill Burns, National Security Councilor Jake Sullivan and the President of the Reunited Major States Charles Brown, among others.
<h2>Tajani calls for reassurance to Iran on Italian soldiers
"I have asked for guarantees to Iran's Foreign Minister for our 1,100 military and I have been told that there will be the greatest attention and responsibility on the part of Iran regarding the Italian military who are deployed between Hezbollah and Israel, between southern Lebanon and northern Israel. On the Iranian side there is a reassurance and a commitment to do everything so that the Italians are absolutely not involved." The Foreign Minister, Antonio Tajani, says that at Tg1.
<h2>Idf: "It's a large-scale attack. Dangerous escalation
"Together with our partners, the IDF is working fully to defend the State of Israel and the people of Israel. This is a mission we are determined and ready to accomplish." It says in a video posted on social networks the spokesman of the IDF, Daniel Hagari, on the current attack from Iran. "We are closely monitoring Iranian killer drones that are on their way to Israel, departed from Iran. This is a serious and dangerous escalation. Our offensive and defensive capacity is at the highest level against this large-scale Iran attack," adds the spokesman.
&nbsp;
<h2>Meloni follows situation in connection with ministers
The President of the Council, Giorgia Meloni, follows the situation in the Middle East and is in contact with the government, with foreign and defence ministers, Antono Tajani and Guido Crosetto, and undersecretary Alfredo Mantovano. It is what is learned from sources of Palazzo Chigi.
<h2>Biden is returned to the White House at 17:02 local </h2>
US President Joe Biden returned to the White House at 17:02. According to the U.S. press, the president arrived in an area far from journalists and entered the Oval Studio without anyone being able to ask him questions.
&nbsp;
<h2>Tehran, drones and missiles against Israel
The Guardians of the Iranian Revolution confirmed that they had launched an attack with drones and missiles against Israel as a retaliation for the killing of seven members, including two generals, shot by the Israelis on 1 April in the consulate of Iran in Damascus, Syria.<br> "In response to the numerous crimes committed by the Zionist regime, including the attack on the consular section. . the Guard Corps of the Islamic Revolution launched dozens of missiles and drones against specific targets within the occupied territories (Israel)", a statement read by state television.
<h2> For Israel more than 100 droni</h2>
Israel estimates that Iran has launched more than 100 drones for the moment. This is reported by the Cnn citing Israeli army officers.
<h2> Iran also launched cruise missiles
Iran has also launched cruise missiles against Israel, which can achieve less targets than drones. Reuters reports it, citing Israeli TV Channel 12.
