AGI - Iran will attack Israel " sooner or later". The alarm was launched by Joe Biden, at the press conference at the White House. "I don't want to enter information covered by secret, but my expectation is that it will happen soon," the President of the United States replied. And who asked him what his message was to Iran right now, Biden replied: "Don't do it." "We are dedicated to the defense of Israel. We will support Israel, we will help defend Israel and Iran will not succeed," he assured the head of the White House. For days, the United States has been alert and feared a significant Iranian attack on Israel > while fears of regionalization of the conflict in the Middle East, after the Israeli attack on an Iranian diplomatic complex in Syria last week, in which three Iranian generals died.
&nbsp;
Biden, who this week warned that Iran was threatening a "significant attack" against Israel, received constant updates on the situation from its national security team. The United States and many other countries, including Italy, Great Britain, Germany and France, have issued new travel guidelines for public employees in Israel > while the Iranian threat was looming. The United States will attempt to intercept any weapon launched against Israel if it is possible to do so, two U.S. officials told Cnn, an indication of the current level of cooperation between the two armies. American Navy forces in the Red Sea have previously intercepted long-range missiles launched by the Houthi in Yemen to Israel.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
U.S. forces in Iraq and Syria could also potentially intercept drones and rockets targeting northern Israel, depending on the location they are launched. The Defence Department is also moving further resources into the Middle East region "to strengthen regional deterrence efforts and increase the protection of the U.S. military," said Cnn an U.S. defense officer, while Israel and the United States are preparing for a potential Iranian attack. The Pentagon has worked specifically to strengthen the air defenses of U.S. troops stationed in Iraq and Syria that have been attacked by proxy forces supported by Iran more than 100 times between October and February. In January, three U.S. military were killed when a drone crossed U.S. air defenses at Tower 22 in Jordan. The United States does not predict that Iran or its delegates will attack the U.S. forces as part of their retaliation, but they are moving resources in any event. "It would be unwise if we did not examine our position in the region to ensure that we are properly prepared," said Kirby.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
U.S. officials told Cnn that such an attack could take place within the week. According to sources close to intelligence, the United States observed military asset movements in Iran, including drones and cruise missiles, signaling the danger of an attack on Israeli targets from within its territory. A source - cited by the broadcaster - reported that the United States had observed Iran prepare at least 100 cruise missiles. It is unclear whether Iran is preparing to strike from its territory as part of an initial attack, or whether it is moving to try to dissuade Israel or the United States from conducting a possible counterattack on its territory. "The threat is very clear and credible," said one of the sources.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"They have set up the bases to lead the attack now. I was just waiting for the right moment." Biden spoke to his Israeli counterpart, Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, of the threat of an Iranian attack on a phone call last week. A direct attack on Israel by Iran is one of the worst scenarios to which the Biden administration is preparing > because it would lead to a rapid escalation of a situation already dramatic in the Middle East. Such an attack could lead the war between Israel and Hamas to become a wider regional conflict, something Biden has long tried to avoid. Biden receives briefing several times a day on the situation, Kirby explained. Kirby said on Friday that U.S. officials are in "consistent communication" with their Israeli counterparts on the issue and that measures are under way to ensure that Israel is able to defend itself. Meanwhile, US Secretary of State Anthony Blinken had telephone conversations with Egyptian and Jordanian colleagues.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;

